<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> I primarily play a warrior, and like so many other warriors I would like to complete my epic quest.  The only problem with this is that the warriors face a bottleneck when it comes to the green scale component.  The green scale currently only drops from two mobs, Severilous and Hoshkar.  Severilous spawns about once a week in Emerald Jungle, and is usually defeated by a group of manaburning wizards within an hour of his spawn, who then sell the scale for more money than most players will ever see (currently selling for 200k on Innoruuk).  Hoshkar exists only in Veeshan's Peak, which makes it a very unlikely source of green scales for the majority of EverQuest players.<br>
<br>
A solution I can see to this, is to restrict this scale to being handled by the players for whom it was intended, the warriors.  That is, make the green scale lootable, tradable, and manageable only by warriors.  In doing so, the manaburn squads that run around extorting money from everybody would be unable to do anything with the scale.  They could take whatever else they wanted, but none of them could handle the scale at all, giving the control over the warrior epic back to the warriors.<br>
<br>
There are of course a few problems with what I am suggesting here.<br>
1. The obvious, the manaburners could just run a warrior twink to the corpse to loot it.  This might be solved by restricting handling of the scale to lvl 46 (or 51) and up.  If they want to loot it, they have to actually work for it.<br>
2. The scale is currently not lore and might result in one lucky warrior cornering the market on the scale.  So, simply make it lore.<br>
3. Make it lore by association (not sure if such a thing is currently possible) with the warrior epic and with the items that result from the scale being turned in in the duration of the epic quest.  That is, a warrior who already has the Jagged Blade of War, The Mark of the Sword, or the Red Scabbard will get the usual lore item message when attempting to loot or receive the scale in a trade.  This would keep the scale in the hands of the needy scaleless warriors (not to say that Iksars don't have needy warriors too).<br>
<br>
I feel that this solution would go a long way in helping to complete the warrior epic quest.  Granted, it'll probably not be implemented exactly as I've laid it out here (if anything is implemented at all in regards to the warrior epic quest), but I hope it might help provide you with ideas on changing this epic.  Certainly the prescient you set by fixing the cleric epic has not gone unnoticed by other classes who's epics have similar bottlenecks (e.g. enchanters with Wraith of a Shissir, rangers with Shattered Emerald of Corruption, etc.).  Also, with Planes of Power right around the corner, I do not feel this would upset the balance of the game at all, considering that weapons which are considered superior to the warrior epic have already been available since Scars of Velious.  I have already made heard it stated that the epics as they are now are Kunark class items, so why not make them more available to players who are similarly at a Kunark class of advancement?<br>
<br>
Thank you for providing me the opportunity to share my ideas on this matter.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=14092">Korby Ubertank</a><br>57 Halfling Myrmidon<br>Unguilded<p>"I was being eatn. I didnt really have time to stick around, sip tea and talk about religion with it." --Envios @ Innoruuk</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ucolwynn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Colwynn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 56<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/14/02 12:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorfrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=575.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: My suggestion on the green scale problem to VI</span><hr size=1> A valiant attempt my friend, but I think it would be more likely if any change was made...it would be to make him triggerable.  As was done recently to Ragefire.  And to keep a reasonable time on the influx of warrior epics...make one of the turn in mobs despawn for a while...again like Rage. <p><center><img src=http://members.rogers.com/hazard/taelensig1.jpg
